Interface NodeWrapper.NodeAttacher

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NodeWrapper.AnchorPaneAttacher, NodeWrapper.BorderPaneAttacher, NodeWrapper.ColRowAttacher, NodeWrapper.DefaultAttacher, NodeWrapper.ListAttacher, NodeWrapper.ListFirstAttacher, NodeWrapper.ListLastAttacher
    Enclosing class:
    NodeWrapper
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface NodeWrapper.NodeAttacher
    Interface for attaching a node to the node wrapper's children at a specified position.
    Author:
    koster

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void attach​(java.lang.Object node, NodeWrapper target)
      Overriding methods must be able to attach the supplied Node to the node wrapper.

    • Method Detail

      • attach

        void attach​(java.lang.Object node,
            NodeWrapper target)
        Overriding methods must be able to attach the supplied Node to the node wrapper.
        Parameters:
        node - the node to attach (not necessarily inheriting from Node (e.g. it is also possible to attach Tabs not inheriting from Node to a TabPane)
        target - the target node that the node shall be attached to
